## Upgrade friction concentrates around security and migration concerns

Accounts with strong feature demand still delayed upgrades when migration effort
and security controls were not addressed in packaging conversations.

Fact: Security and migration concerns repeatedly blocked otherwise qualified upgrade intent.
Belief: Product packaging signals should encode implementation burden explicitly.
Value: Upgrade motions should emphasize risk-managed transition, not only feature breadth.
Precedent: Similar concerns delayed Enterprise conversion in historical product cohorts.
